TWO men aged, 37 and 24, briefly appeared in the Bushbuckridge Magistrates Court on Wednesday, 6 July for allegedly killing, Riot Ubisi (28), a co-founder of the most powerful TSB Security Services. Both were not asked to plead before Magistrate Charles Mokgotho. They were both remanded in custody until 1 August for further investigation and for formal bail application. Brigadier Selvy Mohlala confirmed that the two suspects, who are between the ages 24 and 37, where on 4 June 2022 at 6.15pm passed the victim while on duty and fired shot at him which hit his leg. “The victim was taken to the hospital and the suspects were arrested and charged with attempted murder. But the charges were later changed to murder after the victim succumbed to bullets wounds at the hospital. Both appeared before Bushbuckridge Magistrates Court on Wednesday, facing count of murder. One of the TSB Security Services owners, Norah Sekome said: “Ubisi was busy conducting inspections at the Bushbuckridge shopping complex when the gang fired shots at him on 4 June at around 6.15pm. But he managed to hit back, injuring his attackers. But unfortunately Ubisi died while battling for his life at hospital on 18 June. Meanwhile, a 24-year-old man re-appeared along with his two co-accused, a 27-year-old and 36-year-old in the same court for attacking a victim by assaulting him and stabbing him outside the tavern at Ga-Relane on the 7 May. The 24-year-old was remanded in custody, pending their next appearance on 1 August.